---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Hong Kong Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/hong-kong/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Singapore for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/singapore' },
  { title: 'Taiwan for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/taiwan' },
  { title: 'Malaysia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/malaysia' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'hkFit', header: 'HK Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'HKD 4,200-5,900/mo', hkFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'HKD 4,900-6,900/mo', hkFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'HKD 3,800-5,400/mo', hkFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'HKD 3,500-5,000/mo', hkFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'AXA HK', entryAge: '70', renewal: 'To 100', monthlyFrom: 'HKD 3,000-6,000/mo', hkFit: 'Local Option' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'HKD 3,500-5,900', annual: 'HKD 42,000-70,800' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'HKD 4,900-8,000', annual: 'HKD 58,800-96,000' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'HKD 6,600-10,800', annual: 'HKD 79,200-129,600' },
  { category: 'HK Public Hospital', monthly: 'Subsidized', annual: 'HKD 100/day for residents' },
  { category: 'HK Private Consultation', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: 'HKD 800-2,000/visit' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Hong Kong 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Hong Kong. World-class healthcare, visa requirements, private hospitals, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Hong Kong"
  subheadline="Hong Kong offers world-class healthcare, efficient public transport, incredible food, and international lifestyle—though high costs and limited visa options apply."
  heroImage="/images/countries/hong-kong-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Hong Kong</h2>
  <p>
    Hong Kong offers an unmatched combination: world-class healthcare, incredible food scene, efficient infrastructure, and international atmosphere. English is widely spoken, and the city is extremely safe. For those who enjoy urban energy and Asian culture, Hong Kong delivers uniquely.
  </p>

  <p>
    Hong Kong Island provides iconic skyline and expat community. Kowloon offers more local feel with excellent facilities. The New Territories have hiking and quieter living. Outlying islands like Lantau provide escape from urban density while remaining connected.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; world-class private and good public</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Cantonese/English; English widely used</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> HKD 30,000-60,000/month (~$3,800-7,700); expensive</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Subtropical; hot humid summers, mild winters</li>
      <li><strong>Status:</strong> SAR of China; separate immigration system</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> One of world's safest cities</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Hong Kong's Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Hong Kong has a dual system: excellent public healthcare subsidized for permanent residents, and world-class private healthcare. Public hospitals (Hospital Authority) provide good care at very low cost for residents but involve long wait times. Private hospitals offer premium care with no waits.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private hospitals (Hong Kong Sanatorium, Matilda, Canossa) are expensive but excellent. Many expats use private insurance for these facilities. For non-residents, public hospitals charge full rates (HKD 5,100/day). International insurance is essential for quality care access.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Residency and Healthcare Access</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Hong Kong public healthcare subsidies (HKD 100/day) only apply to permanent residents (7 years residency required). Non-residents pay full rates, making private insurance essential. Without PR, expect to rely on private healthcare or pay full public rates.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Hong Kong's immigration for retirees is limited:
  </p>

  <h3>Capital Investment Entrant Scheme (CIES)</h3>
  <p>
    Restarted in 2024—requires HKD 30 million investment in eligible assets (not property). Provides residence leading to permanent residence after 7 years. High bar but provides pathway.
  </p>

  <h3>Dependant Visa</h3>
  <p>
    If you have Hong Kong permanent resident or employed spouse/children, dependant visa is possible. No financial threshold but sponsor must support you.
  </p>

  <h3>Quality Migrant Admission</h3>
  <p>
    Points-based skilled migrant scheme. Requires high qualifications/achievements. Not designed for retirees but possible for accomplished professionals.
  </p>

  <h3>Visitor Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Most nationalities get 90-180 day visa-free entry. Extended visits possible but not formal residence. Some retirees do "visa runs" but this isn't official residence status.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Hong Kong:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>CIES:</strong> May require health insurance documentation</li>
    <li><strong>Dependant visa:</strong> Sponsor must demonstrate support capacity</li>
    <li><strong>Non-residents:</strong> No public healthcare subsidy; insurance essential</li>
    <li><strong>Private recommended:</strong> Even residents often prefer private care speed</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Hong Kong</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is essential for seniors in Hong Kong—public subsidies only apply after 7 years residency. Private healthcare is excellent but expensive. Ensure coverage includes Hong Kong's private hospitals and sufficient limits (procedures are pricey). Consider plans with direct billing at major hospitals.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Hong Kong, these providers offer strong coverage:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Hong Kong</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong HK network, direct billing at top hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), excellent coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Now Health:</strong> HK-based, local expertise and networks</li>
    <li><strong>AXA HK:</strong> Local option with good private hospital access</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers with strong Hong Kong networks.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Hong Kong are high, reflecting expensive local healthcare:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> HKD 50,000+ deductible reduces premiums</li>
    <li><strong>Asia-only coverage:</strong> Excluding US significantly reduces costs</li>
    <li><strong>Local options:</strong> AXA HK, HSBC Life offer competitive local plans</li>
    <li><strong>Public emergency:</strong> A&E is subsidized; use for emergencies</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American CIES Investor, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> HKD 30M investment. Moving to Hong Kong permanently.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global for comprehensive coverage including US. Direct billing at Hong Kong Sanatorium.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~HKD 5,500/month (~$700). After 7 years, can access public subsidies as backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Dependant, 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Son is HK permanent resident. Dependant visa. UK pension £2,000/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global for comprehensive coverage. Uses Matilda Hospital. UK coverage for visits.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~HKD 7,500/month (~£750). Comfortable with son's support.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Australian Frequent Visitor, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Splits time HK/Australia. Business interests in HK. AUD $4,000/month.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Now Health Asia coverage. Access to HK and Australian providers. Single policy simplicity.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~HKD 4,500/month (~AUD $900). Covers both locations well.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I retire to Hong Kong without HKD 30M?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Difficult officially. The CIES requires HKD 30M investment. Dependant visa needs HK family sponsor. Some do extended visitor stays with visa runs, but this isn't official residence. Quality Migrant Scheme requires high qualifications. There's no simple retirement visa.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How expensive is Hong Kong really?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Housing is extremely expensive—among world's highest. Rent for decent apartment starts HKD 20,000+/month. Food and transport are more reasonable. Healthcare is expensive without insurance. Overall: HKD 40,000-60,000/month for comfortable lifestyle. Housing is the key cost.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Hong Kong still a good place to live?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Depends on priorities. Healthcare, safety, food, and infrastructure remain excellent. Political situation has changed since 2020. Many expats have left; others remain satisfied. It's still one of Asia's most international cities with unique character. Visit and assess personally.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How's the air quality?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Variable. Hong Kong has pollution from regional sources, particularly in winter when winds blow from mainland China. Summer is generally cleaner but hot/humid. Air quality is better than many Asian cities but worse than Singapore. Check AQI forecasts regularly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with strong Hong Kong hospital networks.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/now-health" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Now Health Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Hong Kong Immigration and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
